name.description: Used when building into a model or place

tree.description: The Instance Description of the root instance

servePort.description: Port where rojo serve should listen to

servePlaceIds.description: Place IDs to sync to. This helps to prevent overwriting to incorrect places with the current project.json's source

placeId.description: Sets the current place ID when connecting to Rojo on Roblox Studio

gameId.description: Sets the current game ID when connecting to Rojo on Roblox Studio

serveAddress.description: The web address to serve to. Ex: 127.0.0.1

emitLegacyScripts.description: true = Use Scripts and LocalScripts; false = Use Scripts with RunContext

$path.description: The path on the filesystem to retrieve files

$ignoreUnknownInstances.description: true = ignore instance unknown to Rojo; false = accept unknown instance to Rojo. If path is specified, this option is true
